  cols4-7), and a BOTTOM arena (rows40-62).  Bottom border row63 is colour 7.
- Avatar = colour-14 body + colour-0 head marker (marks facing); moves one 4px
  cell per action; a direction bumped into a wall only re-faces.  Verified it
  can thread the gaps between all three regions.
- Boxes = 4x4, colour-4 border + colour-9 core (thirteen of them).  GRAB =
  face an adjacent box (border 4->3 highlight) then USE (border 3->0, attaches
  rigidly); carry with moves; USE releases (0->3).  Boxes are NOT consumed on
  release.
- Two big 9-bordered / 2-filled SOCKETS (top-right rows8-15 cols44-59; bottom-
  right rows48-59 cols48-59).  A box pushed into a socket's interior stays as a
  4-box; couriers convert a seated box's border 4->5 and stack it in the
  socket's LOADING COLUMN (just inside the left edge).
- FOUR autonomous agents act every turn: two colour-12 COURIERS (seat boxes,
  border 4->5) and two colour-15 MOVERS (steal seated boxes back, 5->4, and
  haul them off, often into the solid colour-2 dead-zone blocks on the left).

Hard budget: ~150 total steps (row-63 colour-7 bar depletes ~1 cell/2.3 steps,
independent of action; terminal at 150).

Why the earlier legs do NOT apply (all verified failing on a level-8 clone):
- Idle (any action) never levels up; free-box count churns 9-13, never ->0;
  socket interior-9 oscillates ~4-18; seated(5-border) count oscillates 1-3.
  So the helpers reach a THIEF-vs-COURIER equilibrium, not completion.
- The colour-15 movers NEVER freeze (max stationary run = 1-2 steps over the
  full budget), so L7's idle_until_mover_frozen + clear_frozen_mover cannot
  neutralise them.  USE next to a MOVING 15 does nothing; the avatar cannot
  step onto / destroy a 15; there is no L6 parked-in-gap clear.
- ferry_all_to_courier_then_yield (L5) and clear_frozen_mover_then_fill (L7)
  both run without a level-up.
- carry_box_to's coarse _grid_scan world model is wrong here: the solid
  colour-2 blocks are NOT walls in that model (only colour-5 is), so its nav
  walks into them and aborts.
- USE is inert against socket-9 borders, solid-2 blocks, and couriers (no
  hidden switch found there).

What was TRIED and still lost (all on clones):
- A pixel-fidelity greedy "grab nearest box, push into nearest socket interior"
  controller (added as the general leg `deliver_boxes_to_sockets`), prefer
